'''Donald E. Burroughs''' ([[August 19]], [[1931]] - [[October 20]], [[2006]]) was an [[American football]] [[defensive back]] in the [[National Football League|NFL]] for the [[Los Angeles Rams]] and the [[Philadelphia Eagles]].  He played [[college football]] at [[Colorado State University]].  Burroughs was notable for his 6'5" height, an anomaly at the safety position. In [[2006]], Burroughs died of cancer.

